212static char *
213add_environ(char ***array, const char *value, int uniq)
214{
215 char **newlist, **list = *array;
216 size_t i = 0, l, lv;
217 char *match = NULL, *p, *n;
218
219 match = strdup(value);
220 if (match == NULL) {
221 logerr(__func__);
222 return NULL;
223 }
224 p = strchr(match, '=');
225 if (p == NULL) {
226 logerrx("%s: no assignment: %s", __func__, value);
227 free(match);
228 return NULL;
229 }
230 *p++ = '\0';
231 l = strlen(match);
232
233 while (list && list[i]) {
234 if (match && strncmp(list[i], match, l) == 0) {
235 if (uniq) {
236 n = strdup(value);
237 if (n == NULL) {
238 logerr(__func__);
239 free(match);
240 return NULL;
241 }
242 free(list[i]);
243 list[i] = n;
244 } else {
245 /* Append a space and the value to it */
246 l = strlen(list[i]);
247 lv = strlen(p);
248 n = realloc(list[i], l + lv + 2);
249 if (n == NULL) {
250 logerr(__func__);
251 free(match);
252 return NULL;
253 }
254 list[i] = n;
255 list[i][l] = ' ';
256 memcpy(list[i] + l + 1, p, lv);
257 list[i][l + lv + 1] = '\0';
258 }
259 free(match);
260 return list[i];
261 }
262 i++;
263 }
264
265 free(match);
266 n = strdup(value);
267 if (n == NULL) {
268 logerr(__func__);
269 return NULL;
270 }
271 newlist = reallocarray(list, i + 2, sizeof(char *));
272 if (newlist == NULL) {
273 logerr(__func__);
274 free(n);
275 return NULL;
276 }
277 newlist[i] = n;
278 newlist[i + 1] = NULL;
279 *array = newlist;
280 return newlist[i];
281}

283#define PARSE_STRING 0
284#define PARSE_STRING_NULL 1
285#define PARSE_HWADDR 2
286#define parse_string(a, b, c) parse_str((a), (b), (c), PARSE_STRING)
287#define parse_hwaddr(a, b, c) parse_str((a), (b), (c), PARSE_HWADDR)
288static ssize_t
289parse_str(char *sbuf, size_t slen, const char *str, int flags)
290{
291 size_t l;
292 const char *p, *end;
293 int i;
294 char c[4], cmd;
295
296 end = str + strlen(str);
297 /* If surrounded by quotes then it's a string */
298 if (*str == '"') {
299 p = end - 1;
300 if (*p == '"') {
301 str++;
302 end = p;
303 }
304 } else {
305 l = (size_t)hwaddr_aton(NULL, str);
306 if ((ssize_t) l != -1 && l > 1) {
307 if (l > slen) {
308 errno = ENOBUFS;
309 return -1;
310 }
311 hwaddr_aton((uint8_t *)sbuf, str);
312 return (ssize_t)l;
313 }
314 }
315
316 /* Process escapes */
317 l = 0;
318 /* If processing a string on the clientid, first byte should be
319 * 0 to indicate a non hardware type */
320 if (flags == PARSE_HWADDR && *str) {
321 if (sbuf)
322 *sbuf++ = 0;
323 l++;
324 }
325 c[3] = '\0';
326 while (str < end) {
327 if (++l > slen && sbuf) {
328 errno = ENOBUFS;
329 return -1;
330 }
331 if (*str == '\\') {
332 str++;
333 switch((cmd = *str++)) {
334 case '\0':
335 str--;
336 break;
337 case 'b':
338 if (sbuf)
339 *sbuf++ = '\b';
340 break;
341 case 'n':
342 if (sbuf)
343 *sbuf++ = '\n';
344 break;
345 case 'r':
346 if (sbuf)
347 *sbuf++ = '\r';
348 break;
349 case 't':
350 if (sbuf)
351 *sbuf++ = '\t';
352 break;
353 case 'x':
354 /* Grab a hex code */
355 c[1] = '\0';
356 for (i = 0; i < 2; i++) {
357 if (isxdigit((unsigned char)*str) == 0)
358 break;
359 c[i] = *str++;
360 }
361 if (c[1] != '\0' && sbuf) {
362 c[2] = '\0';
363 *sbuf++ = (char)strtol(c, NULL, 16);
364 } else
365 l--;
366 break;
367 case '0':
368 /* Grab an octal code */
369 c[2] = '\0';
370 for (i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
371 if (*str < '0' || *str > '7')
372 break;
373 c[i] = *str++;
374 }
375 if (c[2] != '\0' && sbuf) {
376 i = (int)strtol(c, NULL, 8);
377 if (i > 255)
378 i = 255;
379 *sbuf ++= (char)i;
380 } else
381 l--;
382 break;
383 default:
384 if (sbuf)
385 *sbuf++ = cmd;
386 break;
387 }
388 } else {
389 if (sbuf)
390 *sbuf++ = *str;
391 str++;
392 }
393 }
394 if (flags == PARSE_STRING_NULL && sbuf)
395 *sbuf = '\0';
396 return (ssize_t)l;
397}

399static int
400parse_iaid1(uint8_t *iaid, const char *arg, size_t len, int n)
401{
402 int e;
403 uint32_t narg;
404 ssize_t s;
405
406 narg = (uint32_t)strtou(arg, NULL, 0, 0, UINT32_MAX, &e);
407 if (e == 0) {
408 if (n)
409 narg = htonl(narg);
410 memcpy(iaid, &narg, sizeof(narg));
411 return 0;
412 }
413
414 if ((s = parse_string((char *)iaid, len, arg)) < 1)
415 return -1;
416 if (s < 4)
417 iaid[3] = '\0';
418 if (s < 3)
419 iaid[2] = '\0';
420 if (s < 2)
421 iaid[1] = '\0';
422 return 0;
423}

425static int
426parse_iaid(uint8_t *iaid, const char *arg, size_t len)
427{
428
429 return parse_iaid1(iaid, arg, len, 1);
430}

441static char **
442splitv(int *argc, char **argv, const char *arg)
443{
444 char **n, **v = argv;
445 char *o = strdup(arg), *p, *t, *nt;
446
447 if (o == NULL) {
448 logerr(__func__);
449 return v;
450 }
451 p = o;
452 while ((t = strsep(&p, ", "))) {
453 nt = strdup(t);
454 if (nt == NULL) {
455 logerr(__func__);
456 free(o);
457 return v;
458 }
459 n = reallocarray(v, (size_t)(*argc) + 1, sizeof(char *));
460 if (n == NULL) {
461 logerr(__func__);
462 free(o);
463 free(nt);
464 return v;
465 }
466 v = n;
467 v[(*argc)++] = nt;
468 }
469 free(o);
470 return v;
471}

473#ifdef INET
474static int
475parse_addr(struct in_addr *addr, struct in_addr *net, const char *arg)
476{
477 char *p;
478
479 if (arg == NULL || *arg == '\0') {
480 if (addr != NULL)
481 addr->s_addr = 0;
482 if (net != NULL)
483 net->s_addr = 0;
484 return 0;
485 }
486 if ((p = strchr(arg, '/')) != NULL) {
487 int e;
488 intmax_t i;
489
490 *p++ = '\0';
491 i = strtoi(p, NULL, 10, 0, 32, &e);
492 if (e != 0 ||
493 (net != NULL && inet_cidrtoaddr((int)i, net) != 0))
494 {
495 logerrx("`%s' is not a valid CIDR", p);
496 return -1;
497 }
498 }
499
500 if (addr != NULL && inet_aton(arg, addr) == 0) {
501 logerrx("`%s' is not a valid IP address", arg);
502 return -1;
503 }
504 if (p != NULL)
505 *--p = '/';
506 else if (net != NULL && addr != NULL)
507 net->s_addr = ipv4_getnetmask(addr->s_addr);
508 return 0;
509}
510#else
511static int
512parse_addr(__unused struct in_addr *addr, __unused struct in_addr *net,
513 __unused const char *arg)
514{
515
516 logerrx("No IPv4 support");
517 return -1;
518}
519#endif

523 const char *arg,
524 const struct dhcp_opt **d, size_t *dl,

530#if !defined(INET) && !defined(INET6)

534#ifdef INET6

553 *request = ifo->requestmask6;
554 *require = ifo->requiremask6;
555 *no = ifo->nomask6;
556 *reject = ifo->rejectmask6;

559#endif
560#endif
561
562#ifdef INET
563 *d = ctx->dhcp_opts;
564 *dl = ctx->dhcp_opts_len;
565 *od = ifo->dhcp_override;
566 *odl = ifo->dhcp_override_len;

572#endif

574 *require = ifo->requiremask;

580void
581free_dhcp_opt_embenc(struct dhcp_opt *opt)
582{
583 size_t i;
584 struct dhcp_opt *o;
585
586 free(opt->var);
587
588 for (i = 0, o = opt->embopts; i < opt->embopts_len; i++, o++)
589 free_dhcp_opt_embenc(o);
590 free(opt->embopts);
591 opt->embopts_len = 0;
592 opt->embopts = NULL;
593
594 for (i = 0, o = opt->encopts; i < opt->encopts_len; i++, o++)
595 free_dhcp_opt_embenc(o);
596 free(opt->encopts);
597 opt->encopts_len = 0;
598 opt->encopts = NULL;
599}

601static char *
602strwhite(const char *s)
603{
604
605 if (s == NULL)
606 return NULL;
607 while (*s != ' ' && *s != '\t') {
608 if (*s == '\0')
609 return NULL;
610 s++;
611 }
612 return UNCONST(s);
613}

615static char *
616strskipwhite(const char *s)
617{
618
619 if (s == NULL || *s == '\0')
620 return NULL;
621 while (*s == ' ' || *s == '\t') {
622 s++;
623 if (*s == '\0')
624 return NULL;
625 }
626 return UNCONST(s);
627}

629#ifdef AUTH
630/* Find the end pointer of a string. */
631static char *
632strend(const char *s)
633{
634
635 s = strskipwhite(s);
636 if (s == NULL)
637 return NULL;
638 if (*s != '"')
639 return strchr(s, ' ');
640 s++;
641 for (; *s != '"' ; s++) {
642 if (*s == '\0')
643 return NULL;
644 if (*s == '\\') {
645 if (*(++s) == '\0')
646 return NULL;
647 }
648 }
649 return UNCONST(++s);
650}

653static int
654parse_option(struct dhcpcd_ctx *ctx, const char *ifname, struct if_options *ifo,
655 int opt, const char *arg, struct dhcp_opt **ldop, struct dhcp_opt **edop)
656{
657 int e, i, t;
658 long l;
659 unsigned long u;
660 char *p = NULL, *bp, *fp, *np;
661 ssize_t s;
662 struct in_addr addr, addr2;
663 in_addr_t *naddr;
664 struct rt *rt;
665 const struct dhcp_opt *d, *od;
666 uint8_t *request, *require, *no, *reject;
667 struct dhcp_opt **dop, *ndop;
668 size_t *dop_len, dl, odl;
669 struct vivco *vivco;
670 struct group *grp;
671#ifdef AUTH
672 struct token *token;
673#endif
674#ifdef _REENTRANT
675 struct group grpbuf;
676#endif
677#ifdef DHCP6
678 size_t sl;
679 struct if_ia *ia;
680 uint8_t iaid[4];
681#ifndef SMALL
682 struct if_sla *sla, *slap;
683#endif
684#endif
685
686 dop = NULL;
687 dop_len = NULL;
688#ifdef INET6
689 i = 0;
690#endif
691
692/* Add a guard for static analysers.
693 * This should not be needed really because of the argument_required option
694 * in the options declaration above. */
695#define ARG_REQUIRED if (arg == NULL) goto arg_required
696
697 switch(opt) {
698 case 'f': /* FALLTHROUGH */
699 case 'g': /* FALLTHROUGH */
700 case 'n': /* FALLTHROUGH */
701 case 'q': /* FALLTHROUGH */
702 case 'x': /* FALLTHROUGH */
703 case 'N': /* FALLTHROUGH */
704 case 'P': /* FALLTHROUGH */
705 case 'T': /* FALLTHROUGH */
706 case 'U': /* FALLTHROUGH */
707 case 'V': /* We need to handle non interface options */
708 break;
709 case 'b':
710 ifo->options |= DHCPCD_BACKGROUND;
711 break;
712 case 'c':
713 ARG_REQUIRED;
714 if (ifo->script != default_script)
715 free(ifo->script);
716 s = parse_str(NULL, 0, arg, PARSE_STRING_NULL);
717 if (s == 0) {
718 ifo->script = NULL;
719 break;
720 }
721 dl = (size_t)s;

2076#ifdef _REENTRANT
2077 l = sysconf(_SC_GETGR_R_SIZE_MAX);
2078 if (l == -1)
2079 dl = 1024;
2080 else
2081 dl = (size_t)l;
2082 p = malloc(dl);
2083 if (p == NULL) {
2084 logerr(__func__);
2085 return -1;
2086 }
2087 while ((i = getgrnam_r(arg, &grpbuf, p, (size_t)l, &grp)) ==
2088 ERANGE)
2089 {
2090 size_t nl = dl * 2;
2091 if (nl < dl) {
2092 logerrx("control_group: out of buffer");
2093 free(p);
2094 return -1;
2095 }
2096 dl = nl;
2097 np = realloc(p, dl);
2098 if (np == NULL) {
2099 logerr(__func__);
2100 free(p);
2101 return -1;
2102 }
2103 p = np;
2104 }
2105 if (i != 0) {
2106 errno = i;
2107 logerr("getgrnam_r");
2108 free(p);
2109 return -1;
2110 }
2111 if (grp == NULL) {
2112 logerrx("controlgroup: %s: not found", arg);
2113 free(p);
2114 return -1;
2115 }
2116 ctx->control_group = grp->gr_gid;
2117 free(p);
2118#else
2119 grp = getgrnam(arg);
2120 if (grp == NULL) {
2121 logerrx("controlgroup: %s: not found", arg);
2122 return -1;
2123 }
2124 ctx->control_group = grp->gr_gid;
2125#endif
2126 break;
2127 case O_GATEWAY:
2128 ifo->options |= DHCPCD_GATEWAY;
2129 break;
2130 case O_NOUP:
2131 ifo->options &= ~DHCPCD_IF_UP;
2132 break;
2133 case O_SLAAC:
2134 ARG_REQUIRED;
2135 if (strcmp(arg, "private") == 0 ||
2136 strcmp(arg, "stableprivate") == 0 ||
2137 strcmp(arg, "stable") == 0)
2138 ifo->options |= DHCPCD_SLAACPRIVATE;
2139 else
2140 ifo->options &= ~DHCPCD_SLAACPRIVATE;
2141 break;
2142 case O_BOOTP:
2143 ifo->options |= DHCPCD_BOOTP;
2144 break;
2145 case O_NODELAY:
2146 ifo->options &= ~DHCPCD_INITIAL_DELAY;
2147 break;
2148 case O_LASTLEASE_EXTEND:
2149 ifo->options |= DHCPCD_LASTLEASE | DHCPCD_LASTLEASE_EXTEND;
2150 break;
2151 case O_INACTIVE:
2152 ifo->options |= DHCPCD_INACTIVE;
2153 break;
2154 case O_MUDURL:
2155 ARG_REQUIRED;
2156 s = parse_string((char *)ifo->mudurl + 1, MUDURL_MAX_LEN, arg);
2157 if (s == -1) {
2158 logerr("mudurl");
2159 return -1;
2160 }
2161 *ifo->mudurl = (uint8_t)s;
2162 break;
2163 default:
2164 return 0;
2165 }
2166
2167 return 1;
2168
2169#ifdef ARG_REQUIRED
2170arg_required:
2171 logerrx("option %d requires an argument", opt);
2172 return -1;
2173#undef ARG_REQUIRED
2174#endif
2175}

2177static int
2178parse_config_line(struct dhcpcd_ctx *ctx, const char *ifname,
2179 struct if_options *ifo, const char *opt, char *line,
2180 struct dhcp_opt **ldop, struct dhcp_opt **edop)
2181{
2182 unsigned int i;
2183
2184 for (i = 0; i < sizeof(cf_options) / sizeof(cf_options[0]); i++) {
2185 if (!cf_options[i].name ||
2186 strcmp(cf_options[i].name, opt) != 0)
2187 continue;
2188
2189 if (cf_options[i].has_arg == required_argument && !line) {
2190 logerrx("option requires an argument -- %s", opt);
2191 return -1;
2192 }
2193
2194 return parse_option(ctx, ifname, ifo, cf_options[i].val, line,
2195 ldop, edop);
2196 }
2197
2198 logerrx("unknown option: %s", opt);
2199 return -1;
2200}

2202static void
2203finish_config(struct if_options *ifo)
2204{
2205
2206 /* Terminate the encapsulated options */
2207 if (ifo->vendor[0] && !(ifo->options & DHCPCD_VENDORRAW)) {
2208 ifo->vendor[0]++;
2209 ifo->vendor[ifo->vendor[0]] = DHO_END;
2210 /* We are called twice.
2211 * This should be fixed, but in the meantime, this
2212 * guard should suffice */
2213 ifo->options |= DHCPCD_VENDORRAW;
2214 }

2217/* Handy routine to read very long lines in text files.
2218 * This means we read the whole line and avoid any nasty buffer overflows.
2219 * We strip leading space and avoid comment lines, making the code that calls
2220 * us smaller. */
2221static char *
2222get_line(char ** __restrict buf, size_t * __restrict buflen,
2223 FILE * __restrict fp)
2224{
2225 char *p, *c;
2226 ssize_t bytes;
2227 int quoted;
2228
2229 do {
2230 bytes = getline(buf, buflen, fp);
2231 if (bytes == -1)
2232 return NULL;
2233 for (p = *buf; *p == ' ' || *p == '\t'; p++)
2234 ;
2235 } while (*p == '\0' || *p == '\n' || *p == '#' || *p == ';');
2236 if ((*buf)[--bytes] == '\n')
2237 (*buf)[bytes] = '\0';
2238
2239 /* Strip embedded comments unless in a quoted string or escaped */
2240 quoted = 0;
2241 for (c = p; *c != '\0'; c++) {
2242 if (*c == '\\') {
2243 c++; /* escaped */
2244 continue;
2245 }
2246 if (*c == '"')
2247 quoted = !quoted;
2248 else if (*c == '#' && !quoted) {
2249 *c = '\0';
2250 break;
2251 }
2252 }
2253 return p;
2254}

2256struct if_options *
2257default_config(struct dhcpcd_ctx *ctx)
2258{
2259 struct if_options *ifo;
2260
2261 /* Seed our default options */
2262 if ((ifo = calloc(1, sizeof(*ifo))) == NULL) {
2263 logerr(__func__);
2264 return NULL;
2265 }
2266 ifo->options |= DHCPCD_IF_UP | DHCPCD_LINK | DHCPCD_INITIAL_DELAY;
2267 ifo->timeout = DEFAULT_TIMEOUT;
2268 ifo->reboot = DEFAULT_REBOOT;
2269 ifo->script = UNCONST(default_script);
2270 ifo->metric = -1;
2271 ifo->auth.options |= DHCPCD_AUTH_REQUIRE;
2272 TAILQ_INIT(&ifo->routes);
2273#ifdef AUTH
2274 TAILQ_INIT(&ifo->auth.tokens);
2275#endif
2276
2277 /* Inherit some global defaults */
2278 if (ctx->options & DHCPCD_PERSISTENT)
2279 ifo->options |= DHCPCD_PERSISTENT;
2280 if (ctx->options & DHCPCD_SLAACPRIVATE)
2281 ifo->options |= DHCPCD_SLAACPRIVATE;

2286struct if_options *
2287read_config(struct dhcpcd_ctx *ctx,
2288 const char *ifname, const char *ssid, const char *profile)
2289{
2290 struct if_options *ifo;
2291 FILE *fp;
2292 struct stat sb;
2293 char *line, *buf, *option, *p;
2294 size_t buflen;
2295 ssize_t vlen;
2296 int skip, have_profile, new_block, had_block;
2297#ifndef EMBEDDED_CONFIG
2298 const char * const *e;
2299 size_t ol;
2300#endif
2301#if !defined(INET) || !defined(INET6)
2302 size_t i;
2303 struct dhcp_opt *opt;
2304#endif
2305 struct dhcp_opt *ldop, *edop;
2306
2307 /* Seed our default options */
2308 if ((ifo = default_config(ctx)) == NULL)
2309 return NULL;
2310 ifo->options |= DHCPCD_DAEMONISE | DHCPCD_GATEWAY;
2311#ifdef PLUGIN_DEV
2312 ifo->options |= DHCPCD_DEV;
2313#endif
2314#ifdef INET
2315 ifo->options |= DHCPCD_IPV4 | DHCPCD_ARP | DHCPCD_DHCP | DHCPCD_IPV4LL;
2316#endif
2317#ifdef INET6
2318 ifo->options |= DHCPCD_IPV6 | DHCPCD_IPV6RS;
2319 ifo->options |= DHCPCD_IPV6RA_AUTOCONF | DHCPCD_IPV6RA_REQRDNSS;
2320 ifo->options |= DHCPCD_DHCP6;
2321#endif
2322
2323 vlen = dhcp_vendor((char *)ifo->vendorclassid + 1,
2324 sizeof(ifo->vendorclassid) - 1);
2325 ifo->vendorclassid[0] = (uint8_t)(vlen == -1 ? 0 : vlen);
2326
2327 buf = NULL;
2328 buflen = 0;
2329
2330 /* Parse our embedded options file */
2331 if (ifname == NULL && !(ctx->options & DHCPCD_PRINT_PIDFILE)) {
2332 /* Space for initial estimates */
2333#if defined(INET) && defined(INITDEFINES)
2334 ifo->dhcp_override =
2335 calloc(INITDEFINES, sizeof(*ifo->dhcp_override));
2336 if (ifo->dhcp_override == NULL)
2337 logerr(__func__);
2338 else
2339 ifo->dhcp_override_len = INITDEFINES;
2340#endif
2341
2342#if defined(INET6) && defined(INITDEFINENDS)
2343 ifo->nd_override =
2344 calloc(INITDEFINENDS, sizeof(*ifo->nd_override));
2345 if (ifo->nd_override == NULL)
2346 logerr(__func__);
2347 else
2348 ifo->nd_override_len = INITDEFINENDS;
2349#endif
2350#if defined(INET6) && defined(INITDEFINE6S)
2351 ifo->dhcp6_override =
2352 calloc(INITDEFINE6S, sizeof(*ifo->dhcp6_override));
2353 if (ifo->dhcp6_override == NULL)
2354 logerr(__func__);
2355 else
2356 ifo->dhcp6_override_len = INITDEFINE6S;
2357#endif
2358
2359 /* Now load our embedded config */
2360#ifdef EMBEDDED_CONFIG
2361 fp = fopen(EMBEDDED_CONFIG, "r");
2362 if (fp == NULL)
2363 logerr("%s: fopen `%s'", __func__, EMBEDDED_CONFIG);
2364
2365 while (fp && (line = get_line(&buf, &buflen, fp))) {
2366#else
2367 buflen = 80;
2368 buf = malloc(buflen);
2369 if (buf == NULL) {
2370 logerr(__func__);
2371 free_options(ctx, ifo);
2372 return NULL;
2373 }
2374 ldop = edop = NULL;
2375 for (e = dhcpcd_embedded_conf; *e; e++) {
2376 ol = strlen(*e) + 1;
2377 if (ol > buflen) {
2378 char *nbuf;
2379
2380 buflen = ol;
2381 nbuf = realloc(buf, buflen);
2382 if (nbuf == NULL) {
2383 logerr(__func__);
2384 free(buf);
2385 free_options(ctx, ifo);
2386 return NULL;
2387 }
2388 buf = nbuf;
2389 }
2390 memcpy(buf, *e, ol);
2391 line = buf;
2392#endif
2393 option = strsep(&line, " \t");
2394 if (line)
2395 line = strskipwhite(line);
2396 /* Trim trailing whitespace */
2397 if (line) {
2398 p = line + strlen(line) - 1;
2399 while (p != line &&
2400 (*p == ' ' || *p == '\t') &&
2401 *(p - 1) != '\\')
2402 *p-- = '\0';
2403 }
2404 parse_config_line(ctx, NULL, ifo, option, line,
2405 &ldop, &edop);
2406
2407 }
2408
2409#ifdef EMBEDDED_CONFIG
2410 if (fp)
2411 fclose(fp);
2412#endif
2413#ifdef INET
2414 ctx->dhcp_opts = ifo->dhcp_override;
2415 ctx->dhcp_opts_len = ifo->dhcp_override_len;
2416#else
2417 for (i = 0, opt = ifo->dhcp_override;
2418 i < ifo->dhcp_override_len;
2419 i++, opt++)
2420 free_dhcp_opt_embenc(opt);
2421 free(ifo->dhcp_override);
2422#endif
2423 ifo->dhcp_override = NULL;
2424 ifo->dhcp_override_len = 0;
2425
2426#ifdef INET6
2427 ctx->nd_opts = ifo->nd_override;
2428 ctx->nd_opts_len = ifo->nd_override_len;
2429#ifdef DHCP6
2430 ctx->dhcp6_opts = ifo->dhcp6_override;
2431 ctx->dhcp6_opts_len = ifo->dhcp6_override_len;
2432#endif
2433#else
2434 for (i = 0, opt = ifo->nd_override;
2435 i < ifo->nd_override_len;
2436 i++, opt++)
2437 free_dhcp_opt_embenc(opt);
2438 free(ifo->nd_override);
2439 for (i = 0, opt = ifo->dhcp6_override;
2440 i < ifo->dhcp6_override_len;
2441 i++, opt++)
2442 free_dhcp_opt_embenc(opt);
2443 free(ifo->dhcp6_override);
2444#endif
2445 ifo->nd_override = NULL;
2446 ifo->nd_override_len = 0;
2447 ifo->dhcp6_override = NULL;
2448 ifo->dhcp6_override_len = 0;
2449
2450 ctx->vivso = ifo->vivso_override;
2451 ctx->vivso_len = ifo->vivso_override_len;
2452 ifo->vivso_override = NULL;
2453 ifo->vivso_override_len = 0;
2454 }
2455
2456 /* Parse our options file */
2457 fp = fopen(ctx->cffile, "r");
2458 if (fp == NULL) {
2459 /* dhcpcd can continue without it, but no DNS options
2460 * would be requested ... */
2461 logwarn("%s: fopen `%s'", __func__, ctx->cffile);
2462 free(buf);
2463 return ifo;
2464 }
2465 if (stat(ctx->cffile, &sb) == 0)
2466 ifo->mtime = sb.st_mtime;
2467
2468 ldop = edop = NULL;
2469 skip = have_profile = new_block = 0;
2470 had_block = ifname == NULL ? 1 : 0;
2471 while ((line = get_line(&buf, &buflen, fp))) {
2472 option = strsep(&line, " \t");
2473 if (line)
2474 line = strskipwhite(line);
2475 /* Trim trailing whitespace */
2476 if (line) {
2477 p = line + strlen(line) - 1;
2478 while (p != line &&
2479 (*p == ' ' || *p == '\t') &&
2480 *(p - 1) != '\\')
2481 *p-- = '\0';
2482 }
2483 if (skip == 0 && new_block) {
2484 had_block = 1;
2485 new_block = 0;
2486 ifo->options &= ~DHCPCD_WAITOPTS;
2487 }
2488 /* Start of an interface block, skip if not ours */
2489 if (strcmp(option, "interface") == 0) {
2490 char **n;
2491
2492 new_block = 1;
2493 if (line == NULL) {
2494 /* No interface given */
2495 skip = 1;
2496 continue;
2497 }
2498 if (ifname && strcmp(line, ifname) == 0)
2499 skip = 0;
2500 else
2501 skip = 1;
2502 if (ifname)
2503 continue;
2504
2505 n = reallocarray(ctx->ifcv,
2506 (size_t)ctx->ifcc + 1, sizeof(char *));
2507 if (n == NULL) {
2508 logerr(__func__);
2509 continue;
2510 }
2511 ctx->ifcv = n;
2512 ctx->ifcv[ctx->ifcc] = strdup(line);
2513 if (ctx->ifcv[ctx->ifcc] == NULL) {
2514 logerr(__func__);
2515 continue;
2516 }
2517 ctx->ifcc++;
2518 continue;
2519 }
2520 /* Start of an ssid block, skip if not ours */
2521 if (strcmp(option, "ssid") == 0) {
2522 new_block = 1;
2523 if (ssid && line && strcmp(line, ssid) == 0)
2524 skip = 0;
2525 else
2526 skip = 1;
2527 continue;
2528 }
2529 /* Start of a profile block, skip if not ours */
2530 if (strcmp(option, "profile") == 0) {
2531 new_block = 1;
2532 if (profile && line && strcmp(line, profile) == 0) {
2533 skip = 0;
2534 have_profile = 1;
2535 } else
2536 skip = 1;
2537 continue;
2538 }
2539 /* Skip arping if we have selected a profile but not parsing
2540 * one. */
2541 if (profile && !have_profile && strcmp(option, "arping") == 0)
2542 continue;
2543 if (skip)
2544 continue;
2545 parse_config_line(ctx, ifname, ifo, option, line, &ldop, &edop);
2546 }
2547 fclose(fp);
2548 free(buf);
2549
2550 if (profile && !have_profile) {
2551 free_options(ctx, ifo);
2552 errno = ENOENT;
2553 return NULL;
2554 }
2555
2556 if (!had_block)
2557 ifo->options &= ~DHCPCD_WAITOPTS;
2558 finish_config(ifo);
2559 return ifo;
2560}

2562int
2563add_options(struct dhcpcd_ctx *ctx, const char *ifname,
2564 struct if_options *ifo, int argc, char **argv)
2565{
2566 int oi, opt, r;
2567 unsigned long long wait_opts;
2568
2569 if (argc == 0)
2570 return 1;
2571
2572 optind = 0;
2573 r = 1;
2574 /* Don't apply the command line wait options to each interface,
2575 * only use the dhcpcd.conf entry for that. */
2576 if (ifname != NULL)
2577 wait_opts = ifo->options & DHCPCD_WAITOPTS;
2578 while ((opt = getopt_long(argc, argv,
2579 ctx->options & DHCPCD_PRINT_PIDFILE ? NOERR_IF_OPTS : IF_OPTS,
2580 cf_options, &oi)) != -1)
2581 {
2582 r = parse_option(ctx, ifname, ifo, opt, optarg, NULL, NULL);
2583 if (r != 1)
2584 break;
2585 }
2586 if (ifname != NULL) {
2587 ifo->options &= ~DHCPCD_WAITOPTS;
2588 ifo->options |= wait_opts;
2589 }
2590
2591 finish_config(ifo);
2592 return r;
2593}
